1- User comes to UI types in a prompt
2- UI service calls LLM (AWS Bedrock), LLM analyzes prompt and decides MCP tool to call
3- Lambda function to call our MCP server with the correct tool (Need to test/verify) - If not lambda, UI can grab response from LLM and call MCP server directly
4- MCP calls sherlock with specified tool from previous stage
5- Sherlock responds back to MCP with json
6- MCP sends json back to UI
7- UI layer sends the json + prompt to LLM, displays to user
 
User enters prompt in UI

UI sends prompt to backend orchestrator

Orchestrator calls LLM (Bedrock) with MCP tool schema

LLM returns tool call proposal

Orchestrator calls MCP server with tool + args

MCP calls Sherlock and gets JSON

Orchestrator sends tool result back to LLM

LLM returns final answer

UI displays response
